There are five low-income people who have decided to seek a loan for different purposes. One of these people, Mr. R., 39, has been chosen to be the leader of this loan group by the other members. Most of R.’s life is spent on the river fishing with his wife in order to earn an income. They typically generate a daily profit of $6 to contribute their family’s living expenses. R. said that he feels so happy in his current work. It is a profitable one for his family, but unfortunately, some of his fishing tools are broken. He would like a loan to buy new fishing tools and to repair some broken pieces. R. proposes to use some of the loan to buy a machine to connect with his existing boat for fishing. The other members of this group loan are:
Mrs. S., who is pursuing a loan to finish building her new house;
Mrs. N., a fish catcher, who is asking for a loan to buy more fishing equipment;
Mr. C., a fisherman who will use his loan to repair his old house; and
Mrs. P., who will use this Kiva loan to mend her broken house.
